{{Infobox language |name=Mesqan |altname= |pronunciation= |states=[[Ethiopia]] |region=[[Gurage Zone]] |speakers={{sigfig|195,000|2}} |date=2007 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Afro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Semitic languages|Semitic]] |fam3=[[South Semitic languages|South]] |fam4=[[Ethiopian Semitic languages|Ethiopian]] |fam5=South |fam6=Outer |fam7=tt-Group |iso3=mvz |glotto=mesq1240 |glottorefname=Mesqan |script=none }} '''Mesqan''' (also '''Mäsqan''' or '''Meskan''') is an [[Afroasiatic languages|Afro-Asiatic]] language spoken by the [[Gurage people]] in the [[Gurage Zone]] of [[Ethiopia]]. It belongs to the family's [[Ethiopian Semitic languages|Ethiopian Semitic]] branch.
