{{Infobox website | name = {{Wiki favicon}} Silesian Wikipedia | logo = [[File:Wikipedia-logo-v2-szl.svg|Logo of the Silesian Wikipedia]] | screenshot = [[File:Silesian Wikipedia (December 2009).JPG|280px|The [[Main Page]] of the Polish Wikipedia (06.12.2009).]] | caption = The [[Main Page]] of the Silesian Wikipedia (December 2009). | collapsible = yes | url = [http://szl.wikipedia.org szl.wikipedia.org] | commercial = No. [[Charity (practice)|Charitable]] | launch date = 26 May 2008 | type = [[Internet encyclopedia project]] | language = [[Silesian language|Silesian]] | registration = Optional | owner = [[Wikimedia Foundation]] |}} '''Silesian Wikipedia''' ({{lang-szl|{{#property:P1448}}}}) is the [[Silesian language|Silesian]] edition of [[Wikipedia]]. It was started on 26 May 2008.
== History == [[File:Silesian Wikipedia screenshot - 2008-05-26.png|thumb|left|250px|Screen of first day of action Silesian Wikipedia]] The first attempt to launch the Silesian Wikipedia project took place in March 2006,<ref>{{pl icon}} [[Gazeta Wyborcza]]: [http://gospodarka.gazeta.pl/gospodarka/1,68367,3098544.html "''Będzie Wikipedia po śląsku?''"], 2006</ref> but because of negative comments in the discussion section, the proposal was rejected.<ref>{{en icon}} http://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Requests_for_new_languages/Wikipedia_Upper_Silesian</ref> In 2007 Wikipedia officially registered the Silesian language in its list of languages.{{Clarify|date=January 2014}} The International Linguistic Organization [[SIL International]] followed this step on 18 July 2007 and [[International Organization for Standardization]] (ISO) assigned it the ISO code "szl".<ref>{{en icon}} [http://www.sil.org/iso639-3/documentation.asp?id=szl www.sil.org] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121003061821/http://www.sil.org/iso639-3/documentation.asp?id=szl |date=2012-10-03 }} - ISO documentation of Silesian language</ref><ref>{{en icon}} [http://www.sil.org/iso639-3/codes.asp?order=639_3&letter=s www.sil.org] - list of languages with codes ISO (letter "S")</ref><ref>{{en icon}} [http://www.ethnologue.org/codes/LanguageCodes.tab www.ethnologue.org] - list of languages with codes ISO</ref><ref>{{en icon}} [http://www.lingvoj.org/lingvo/szl www.lingvoj.org]</ref>
A second application for a Wikipedia project in the Silesian language was submitted on 19 March 2008<ref>{{en icon}} http://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Requests_for_new_languages/Wikipedia_Silesian</ref> as a result of discussions on the removal of articles written in Silesian language, which remained in the Polish edition of Wikipedia (in Silesia Wikiproject).<ref>{{pl icon}} http://pl.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:SDU/Kategoria:%C5%9Al%C4%85ska_Wikipedia</ref><ref>{{pl icon}} [[Gazeta Wyborcza]]: [http://miasta.gazeta.pl/katowice/1,35019,4042539.html?skad=rss "''Narodziła się śląska Wikipedia''"], 05.04.2007</ref> After the initial acceptance of the proposal (100% positive, 0% negative votes) 31 March 2008, a test project was created in the Incubator Wikimedia projects. The following month it contained 100 articles in Silesian, including more than 1,800 separate pages. After two months all eight requirements necessary to create a new Wikipedia were implemented and finally Silesian Wikipedia was founded on 26 May 2008.<ref>{{pl icon}} [[Gazeta Wyborcza]]: [http://miasta.gazeta.pl/katowice/1,35019,5251398.html "''Jest już Wikipedia po śląsku''"], 27.05.2008</ref><ref>{{pl icon}} [[Gazeta Wyborcza]]: [http://gospodarka.gazeta.pl/IT/1,88732,5248211,Slaska_Wikipedia_juz_dziala.html "''Śląska Wikipedia już działa''"], 27.05.2008</ref><ref>{{pl icon}} [[Dziennik Zachodni]]: "''Świat po naszymu, ślonsko godka w wikipedii''", 31.05.2008</ref><ref>{{pl icon}} [[Radio Plus (Poland)|Radio Plus]]: [http://www.plus.gliwice.pl/news.php?type=news&id=3950 "''Śląska Wikipedia''"]{{dead link|date=May 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, 29.05.2008</ref><ref>{{pl icon}} [[TV Silesia]]: [http://www.tvs.pl/informacje/1524/ "''Śląska Wikipedia''"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080529143935/http://www.tvs.pl/informacje/1524/ |date=2008-05-29 }}, 28.05.2008</ref><ref>{{pl icon}} Radio [[TOK FM]]: [http://bi.gazeta.pl/im/4/5254/m5254794.mp3 "''"Wikipedia po śląsku"''"], 28.05.2008</ref><ref>{{pl icon}} [[Radio eM]]: [http://www.radioem.pl/?page=news&cat=region&mode=single&id=13451 "''Wikipedia po śląsku''"], 29.05.2008</ref><ref>{{pl icon}} [[TVP1]] - [[Teleexpress]]: mention about create Silesian Wikipedia, 29.05.2008</ref> The 1,000th article was included on 15 November 2008.
In October 2010 the Silesian Wikipedia was mentioned as one of the arguments for Silesian to become one of the regional languages in Poland. The project of the law implementing Silesian as a regional language was introduced to Sejm by parliament member [[Marek Plura]].<ref>{{pl icon}} [http://wyborcza.pl/1,91446,8593341,Projekt_ustawy_wprowadzajacej_slaski_jako_jezyk_regionalny.html Projekt ustawy wprowadzającej śląski jako język regionalny - w Sejmie]</ref>
