{{for|the island|Teanu island}} {{Infobox language |name=Teanu |nativename = Teanu |states=[[Solomon Islands]] |region=[[Vanikoro]], Eastern Solomons |coordinates = {{coord|11|39|S|166|54|E|type:landmark|display=inline}} |speakers=800 |date=2012 |ref=<ref>[http://alex.francois.free.fr/AF-field.htm#Solomons List of Vanikoro languages] (homepage of linguist [[Alexandre François (linguist)|A. François]]).</ref> |familycolor=Austronesian |fam2=[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] |fam3=[[Oceanic languages|Oceanic]] |fam4=[[Temotu languages|Temotu]] |fam5=[[Utupua–Vanikoro languages|Utupua–Vanikoro]] |fam6=[[Vanikoro languages|Vanikoro]] |iso3=tkw |glotto=tean1237 |glottorefname=Teanu }}
'''Teanu''' (or ''Puma'', ''Buma'') is the main language spoken on the island of [[Vanikoro]], in the easternmost province of the [[Solomon Islands]].
Some information on Teanu, as well as on the two other languages of the island, can be found in {{Harvcoltxt|François|2009}}.
==Name== The language receives its name from [[Teanu island|Teanu]], the island located northeast of the Vanikoro island group. The same language has also been known in the literature as ''Puma'' (or wrongly ''Buma''), after the [[Puma village|main village]] of Teanu island.<ref name="F2009">{{Harvcoltxt|François|2009}}.</ref>
==Geography== Whereas Teanu used to be confined to the northeast part of the island group, during the 20th century it has become the main language of the whole island group of Vanikoro, at the expense of the two other indigenous languages [[Lovono]] and [[Tanema]].<ref name="F2009"/>
While the Melanesian population of [[Vanikoro]] now speaks Teanu, the southern coast of the island also has been colonised for a few centuries by a [[Polynesia]]n population, who still keep strong ties with their homeland, the nearby island of [[Tikopia]]. Their main language is [[Tikopia language|Tikopia]], even though some speak Teanu as a second language.
==Phonology== Teanu has 5 [[phoneme|phonemic]] vowels, /i e a o u/.<ref>{{Harvcoltxt|François|2009|p=107}}.</ref> {|class="wikitable" !&nbsp; ! [[Front vowel|Front]] ! [[Back vowel|Back]] |- ![[Close vowel|Close]] | align=center | {{IPA|i}} | align=center | {{IPA|u}} |- ![[Close-mid vowel|Close-mid]] | align=center | {{IPA|e}} | align=center | {{IPA|o}} |- ![[Open vowel|Open]] | colspan="2" style="text-align:center;"| {{IPA|a}} |}
