'''Yedina''', also known as '''Buduma''' (Boudouma), is a [[Chadic language]] of the [[Biu–Mandara]] branch spoken around [[Lake Chad]] in western [[Chad]] and neighbouring [[Cameroon]] and [[Nigeria]].<ref name=e18/>

